hasAttributes.name: EmissionFactorId
hasAttributes.description: Unique identifier either coming from previous system otherwise it needs to be define

hasAttributes.name: Name
hasAttributes.description: User specific emission factor name (this can also be the name of a scenario)

hasAttributes.name: Country
hasAttributes.description: Sovereign nations and their dependent territories, anything with anÂ ISO-3166 ALPHA-2 code

hasAttributes.name: Type
hasAttributes.description: Specific type of emission factor e.g. district heating or water discharge

hasAttributes.name: ValidFrom
hasAttributes.description: The records can be used from this date onwards in yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ssZ form (conform to ISO 8061)

hasAttributes.name: ValidUntil
hasAttributes.description: The records can be used until this date in yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ssZ form (conform to ISO 8061)

hasAttributes.name: Unit
hasAttributes.description: Unit of emission factor in terms of kgCO2e per unit of resource consumption

hasAttributes.name: Source
hasAttributes.description: Source of emission factor e.g. 'International Energy Agency'

hasAttributes.name: SpaceType
hasAttributes.description: Differentiated emission factor for certain space type (within a building)

hasAttributes.name: Region
hasAttributes.description: Areas that are broadly divided by physical characteristics, human impact characteristics, and the interaction of humanity and the environment

hasAttributes.name: City
hasAttributes.description: Any official settlement including cities, towns, villages, hamlets, localities, etc

definitions.description: Emission factors that are applied to convert energy consumption data into greenhouse gas emissions. The entity also includes global warming potential data for non-CO2 greenhouse gases in order to calculate CO2-equivalents (CO2e)
